    <section class="card">
      <h2>Orientation</h2>
      <p>
        The Book of Daniel is the prophetic bedrock of the New Testament. It provides the exact chronological roadmap from the Babylonian exile down to the arrival of the Messiah and the destruction of the Old Covenant temple system. 
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Futurism shatters the timeline of Daniel</strong> by inserting an arbitrary, unbiblical 2,000-year "gap" into the 70 Weeks prophecy to delay the Kingdom of God. This module reclaims Daniel by demonstrating that the stone cut without hands (Christ's Kingdom) struck the statue exactly when Daniel said it would: in the days of the fourth empire (first-century Rome). The prophecies of Daniel were sealed until the time of the end—which arrived precisely in AD 70 when the power of the holy people was finally shattered.
      </p>
    </section>

